<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Nias_language&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1" title="Edit section: Grammar">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Grammar">Grammar</span></h2>
<p>The basic <a href="/wiki/Word_order" title="Word order">word order</a> in Nias is <a href="/wiki/Verb_Object_Subject" title="Verb Object Subject">Verb Object Subject</a>, a characteristic shared with <a href="/wiki/Malagasy_language" title="Malagasy language">Malagasy</a> and the <a href="/wiki/Batak_languages" title="Batak languages">Batak languages</a>. There are no <a href="/wiki/Adjective" title="Adjective">adjectives</a> in Nias, instead <a href="/wiki/Verb" title="Verb">verbs</a> are used in their place.<sup id="cite_ref-Brown2005_2-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Brown2005-2"><span>[</span>3<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<p>Nias shows <a href="/wiki/Consonant_mutation" title="Consonant mutation">consonant mutation</a> at the beginning of <a href="/wiki/Noun" title="Noun">nouns</a> and some other classes of words to show <a href="/wiki/Grammatical_case" title="Grammatical case">grammatical case</a>. Several consonants are subject to mutation as shown in the table below. Where a word begins in a vowel, either <i>n</i> or <i>g</i> is added before the vowel.<sup id="cite_ref-Brown2005_2-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Brown2005-2"><span>[</span>3<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<table class="wikitable" border="1">
<caption>Initial mutations</caption>
<tr style="background: #efefef;">
<th scope="col">Base form</th>
<th scope="col">Mutated form</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="center"><i>f</i></td>
<td align="center"><i>v</i></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="center"><i>t</i></td>
<td align="center"><i>d</i></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="center"><i>s</i></td>
<td align="center" rowspan="2"><i>z</i></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="center"><i>c</i></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="center"><i>k</i></td>
<td align="center"><i>g</i></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="center"><i>b</i></td>
<td align="center"><i>mb</i></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="center"><i>d</i></td>
<td align="center"><i>ndr</i></td>
</tr>
